Package: kdetoys
Architecture: all
Section: kde
Depends: amor (>= ${source:Version}), eyesapplet (>= ${source:Version}), fifteenapplet (>= ${source:Version}), kmoon (>= ${source:Version}), kteatime (>= ${source:Version}), ktux (>= ${source:Version}), kweather (>= ${source:Version}), kworldclock (>= ${source:Version})
Description: toys from the official KDE4 release
 KDE (the K Desktop Environment) is a powerful Open Source graphical
 desktop environment for Unix workstations. It combines ease of use,
 contemporary functionality, and outstanding graphical design with the
 technological superiority of the Unix operating system.
 .
 This metapackage includes a collection of toys and fun extras provided
 with the official release of KDE4.


Package: amor
Architecture: any
Section: games
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Recommends: kwin
Suggests: khelpcenter
Description: a KDE creature for your desktop
 AMOR stands for Amusing Misuse Of Resources. It provides several different
 characters who prance around your X screen doing tricks and giving you tips.
 .
 This package is part of KDE, and a component of the KDE4 toys module.
 See the 'kde' and 'kdetoys' packages for more information.

Package: eyesapplet
Architecture: any
Section: kde
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: eyes applet for KDE4
 An applet for the KDE panel containing a pair of eyes that follow your mouse
 around the screen.
 .
 This package is part of KDE, and a component of the KDE4 toys module.
 See the 'kde' and 'kdetoys' packages for more information.

Package: fifteenapplet
Architecture: any
Section: kde
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: fifteen pieces puzzle for KDE4
 An applet for the KDE panel that lets you play the Fifteen Pieces
 sliding block puzzle. You have to order 15 pieces in a 4x4 square by
 moving them around.
 .
 This package is part of KDE, and a component of the KDE4 toys module.
 See the 'kde' and 'kdetoys' packages for more information.

